<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRIC MEASURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding "U.S. Inching Toward Metric System" (Part Am April 7): Maybe slowly, 
but the meter is still running. 
</P>
<P>
Have you used any inch-and-three-eighths film lately: You'd probably answer 
more quickly if I asked "any 35-millimeter film." That's metric. 
</P>
<P>
We use the metric system a lot more than we realize. Our cars are marked with 
little metric measurements -- 1.9, 3.6 or whatever. Most packaged or canned 
foods, frozen dinners, bottled goods show metric measures. Vodka? Champagne? 
Even the bottles have changed to metric sizes. Even the labels seem to be 
saying "Take me to your liter!" 
</P>
<P>
IRVIN BORDERS 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
