<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: UCSD REMAINS UNBEATEN; ADVANCES IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC San Diego remained undefeated and advanced to the NCAA Water Polo 
Championship's with a 10-5 victory Sunday over UC Davis in the finals of the 
Western Regional Qualifying tournament at UCSD. 
</P>
<P>
UCSD (17-0-1) took a 9-1 lead into the fourth period and held off UC Davis, 
which also received an automatic bid to the NCAA tournament in Providence, 
R.I., May 4-6. 
</P>
<P>
UC Santa Barbara defeated Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, 13-8, for third place and 
Cal defeated Long Beach State, 19-8, in the fifth place game. 
</P>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
The seventh McMillin Realty Corporate Challenge volleyball tournament will be 
held Saturday, May 12 at the Del Mar Race Track. 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds will benefit the U.S. men's and women's volleyball teams. 
</P>
<P>
Registration forms can be obtained by calling 692-4162. A $350 entry fee is 
required for all entrants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
