<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN COURT: A SUMMARY OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA-RELATED BUSINESS LITIGATION 
DEVELOPMENTS DURING THE PAST WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Playboy Sued Over Betty Boop Cartoon: The creator and copyright owner of Betty 
Boop filed a copyright infringement suit against Playboy Enterprises, which 
used a fully clothed drawing of the cartoon character to illustrate an article 
called "Return of the Designing Woman." 
</P>
<P>
The suit, brought in U.S. District Court in Los Angeles, said the use of Betty 
Boop falsely gave the impression that Fleischer Studios Inc. of New York 
authorized or endorsed Playboy magazine. The suit seeks unspecified damages of 
at least $100,000. (Filed April 9, 1990. Case No. 90-1767) 
</P>
