IN COURT: A SUMMARY OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA-RELATED BUSINESS LITIGATION 
DEVELOPMENTS DURING THE PAST WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sizzler Sues Over Licensing Agreements: Sizzler Restaurants International sued 
two Illinois firms in U.S. District Court, claiming that they violated 
licensing agreements concerning 21 Sizzler restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
The breach of contract and trademark suit said FBC Food Services Inc. and 
Midwest Restaurant Concepts Inc. opened Sizzler restaurants as licensees but 
failed to pay charges relating to gross sales and advertising. The suit seeks 
unspecified damages and a court order barring the Illinois-based defendants 
from operating Sizzlers. The defendants could not be reached for comment. 
(Filed April 11, 1990. Case No. 90-1820) 
