<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yale Repertory Lineup: Lloyd Richards, artistic director of the Yale Repertory 
Theatre, announced three plays for his last season with the company. 
</P>
<P>
Opening the 1990-91 season will be the American debut of the Moscow Art 
Theatre's production of Anton Chekhov's "Ivanov." Also included in the season 
is the East Coast premiere of Howard Korder's "Search and Destroy," and the 
American premiere of Joshua Sobol's "Underground." Richards announced earlier 
this year he would be stepping down to pursue other interests, including acting 
and directing. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA041690-0077 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 205181 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 16, 1990, Monday, Home Edition 
