<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dick Dale and the Del-Tones will play at Earth Day observance Sunday at 
Centennial Regional Park, Edinger Avenue and Fairview Street in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
Admission to "Earthfestival" will be free to those who ride a bike or take the 
bus, or who bring a shopping bag with recyclable aluminum, glass, plastic or 
newspapers. Alternate admission: $1. The event will run from 8 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
with Dale playing at 2:15. Other entertainment will be offered, along with 
informational exhibits. Part of "The Tell" will be on display; the huge, 
now-dismantled photomural was constructed last year along Laguna Canyon Road, 
where it became a rallying point for those opposed to the area's development. 
</P>
