<P>
MISSING 2-YEAR-OLD BOY FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 2-year-old boy missing 16 hours after disappearing from an Easter carnival at 
a Sunland park was found this morning wandering in a Panorama City parking lot 
about 10 miles away, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Jesse Salazar of Sunland appeared to be unharmed and was in good spirits when 
reunited with his parents, Patricia and Jesse Salazar Sr., at Sunland Park 
about 10:15 a.m. Police said the boy will undergo a medical examination to 
determine if he was injured. 
</P>
<P>
When a police car pulled into the park and the boy was handed over to his 
mother and father, he was immediately surrounded by a crush of relatives and 
media. Several of the relatives were crying as they kissed the boy or called, 
"Hi, Jesse! Hi, Jesse!" 
</P>
<P>
Although they said the boy could not have walked from Sunland to Panorama City, 
police stopped short of calling the boy's disappearance a kidnaping. Police 
said the boy is too young to tell them what happened. 
</P>
