<TEXT>
<P>
The National, the sports daily that has been publishing editions in New York, 
Chicago and Los Angeles for the last 2 1/2 months, plans to begin editions this 
summer in San Diego and San Francisco, officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
Publisher Peter Price said in a telephone interview that he expects the San 
Diego edition to start by July 1 and that a San Francisco edition will be 
launched in July. 
</P>
<P>
He said the newspaper plans to add at least one city a month to its lineup 
during the last five months of the year, but was not ready to identify the 
cities. 
</P>
<P>
The National, which offers coverage of national sports supplemented with local 
sports in each city where it appears, debuted Jan. 31. 
</P>
<P>
It is now distributing an average of about 350,000 newspapers a day and selling 
more than 200,000 copies a day, Price said. 
