<P>
POLLY BERGEN FILES FOR DIVORCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actress Polly Bergen, perhaps best known to television audiences for her 
Emmy-nominated role as Rhoda in "War and Remembrance" and the sequel "The Winds 
of War," has filed for divorce. 
</P>
<P>
Bergen filed a Superior Court petition in Los Angeles today to end her 
eight-year marriage to New York entrepreneur Jeffrey Endervelt. 
</P>
<P>
The court documents cited "irreconcilable differences" as the reason for the 
split. 
</P>
<P>
Bergen, 60, and Endervelt, 50, maintained homes on both coasts and had no 
children, said Marilyn Reiss, publicist for Bergen. 
</P>
<P>
The actress was nominated for two Emmy Awards, one for "The Winds of War" and 
the other for "War and Remembrance." Rhoda was the wife of naval officer Pug 
Henry in the miniseries. 
</P>
<P>
Bergen is in Louisiana today, working on the CBS-TV pilot "Steel Magnolias," 
based on the movie, Reiss said. 
</P>
